{"title": "Golden Book of Springfield", "description": "<i>The Golden Book of Springfield</i> is American poet Vachel Lindsay's strange and mystical odyssey through the Springfield, Illinois of 2018, where the residents of that city strive to turn their home into a democratic utopia. It is a \"Springfield a hundred years hence,\" a dreamlike space of spiritual and social awakenings. But when the threat of international war begins to loom over the horizon, the citizens of Springfield must find new ways to protect their city and keep it a \"practical City of God.\"<br /><br />\n\nThis is Vachel Lindsay's only long-form narrative work and a fascinating entry into the utopian fiction subgenre that came about after the publication of Edward Bellamy's <i>Looking Backward</i>. - Summary by Chuck Williamson", "duration": 33738, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "2123", "name": "Vachel Lindsay"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/goldenbookofspringfield_1807_librivox/golden_book_springfield_1807.jpg", "copyright_year": "1920", "genres": ["Culture & Heritage Fiction", "Fantasy Fiction"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Chuck Williamson"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Chuck Williamson"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "TriciaG"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "DaveC"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "Chapter I - The Campbellite, the Florist, and the Hostess", "readers": [7079], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/goldenbookofspringfield_1807_librivox/goldenbookofspringfield_01_lindsay_64kb.mp3", "duration": 681}, {"section": 2, "title": "Chapter II - The Prognosticator's Club", "readers": [7079], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/goldenbookofspringfield_1807_librivox/goldenbookofspringfield_02_lindsay_64kb.mp3", "duration": 818}, {"section": 3, "title": "Chapter III - How People in 1920 Think the Book Will Come, in 2018", "readers": [7079], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/goldenbookofspringfield_18